WEBVTT

00:02.836 --> 00:04.837
[HORNS HONKING]

00:04.839 --> 00:06.839
[♪]

00:12.862 --> 00:16.749
CLEVELAND:
<i>♪ When the day is long</i>

00:18.284 --> 00:20.736
<i>♪ And the night</i>

00:20.738 --> 00:23.939
<i>♪ The night is yours alone</i>

00:27.911 --> 00:33.748
<i>♪ When you're sure</i>
<i>You've had enough ♪</i>

00:33.750 --> 00:36.518
<i>♪ Of this life</i>

00:37.620 --> 00:39.321
<i>♪ Hang on</i>

00:43.293 --> 00:48.147
<i>♪ Don't let yourself go ♪</i>

00:51.317 --> 00:56.254
<i>♪ 'Cause everybody cries ♪</i>

00:58.792 --> 01:03.028
<i>♪ And everybody hurts</i>

01:03.930 --> 01:05.364
[MUSIC STOPS]

01:05.366 --> 01:08.000
You've given me an idea.
No time to waste.

01:08.002 --> 01:10.235
Wait, do you still have
that Moses staff?

01:10.237 --> 01:12.204
Sure do.

01:16.175 --> 01:20.212
And...part!

01:21.998 --> 01:23.616
Had it backwards.
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

01:23.618 --> 01:27.219
Terry, do I have
tiny Jews in my hair?

01:27.221 --> 01:29.254
Yeah, it looks like it.
[LAUGHS]

01:30.590 --> 01:32.841
♪ My name is Cleveland Brown

01:32.843 --> 01:35.110
♪ And I am proud to be

01:35.112 --> 01:37.495
♪ Right back
In my hometown ♪

01:37.497 --> 01:39.882
♪ With my new family

01:39.884 --> 01:42.367
♪ There's old friends
And new friends ♪

01:42.369 --> 01:44.503
♪ And even a bear

01:44.505 --> 01:46.805
♪ Through good times
And bad times ♪

01:46.807 --> 01:48.406
♪ It's true love we share ♪

01:48.408 --> 01:50.643
♪ And so I found a place

01:50.645 --> 01:52.778
♪ Where everyone will know

01:52.780 --> 01:55.014
♪ My happy mustache face

01:55.016 --> 01:57.116
♪ This is <i>The Cleveland Show</i> ♪

01:57.118 --> 01:59.218
[LAUGHS]

01:59.220 --> 02:02.588
[♪]

02:02.590 --> 02:04.623
The Spanish ice cream
truck's back.

02:04.625 --> 02:07.226
Let's buy some pot.

02:08.361 --> 02:10.428
Oh, just Cleveland.

02:10.430 --> 02:12.164
Hey, can we buy some pot?

02:12.166 --> 02:14.633
Marijuana is illegal
and immoral.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.068
No, wait. That's cocaine.

02:16.070 --> 02:17.970
No,
I don't have any marijuana.

02:17.972 --> 02:22.107
I am here to talk to you about
selling beer on the freeway.

02:22.109 --> 02:24.876
That's right,
I've invented a beer truck.

02:24.878 --> 02:27.813
The business strategy
is in your investment packets.

02:28.764 --> 02:29.832
I'm in.
Me too.

02:29.834 --> 02:32.801
I just gotta show
this to my lawyer.

02:32.803 --> 02:34.236
I don't know Cleveland.

02:34.238 --> 02:35.754
It's just that me and Kendra

02:35.756 --> 02:37.222
have been sort of
in-between jobs

02:37.224 --> 02:38.590
for the last 34 years.

02:38.592 --> 02:40.024
Money's a little tight.

02:40.026 --> 02:42.394
But if you invest
what little money you have

02:42.396 --> 02:43.829
in my beer truck idea,

02:43.831 --> 02:47.666
you're guaranteed to make
a million dollars or less.

02:47.668 --> 02:49.584
Fine. I'll ask my wife.

02:49.586 --> 02:52.337
Oh, yeah. If there are two
things women are great at,

02:52.339 --> 02:55.440
it's managing money
and not killing dreams.

02:55.442 --> 02:56.891
Ha.

02:59.295 --> 03:00.562
[ALL LAUGHING]

03:03.966 --> 03:06.734
So I thought
if I took our savings,

03:06.736 --> 03:09.354
our couch money,
and redeemed our Camel bucks--

03:09.356 --> 03:12.474
But that scrilla's gotta
last us our whole lives.

03:12.476 --> 03:16.678
I mean, what are the odds
of me falling in Walmart again?

03:16.680 --> 03:18.346
Please.

03:18.348 --> 03:21.366
No, Lester. The answer is no.

03:21.368 --> 03:25.003
Now, why don't you get
in here with me?

03:25.005 --> 03:26.738
How?

03:26.740 --> 03:29.624
[♪]

03:32.661 --> 03:34.629
[LAUGHING]

03:34.631 --> 03:37.516
Come on, Rallo. You're up.

03:37.518 --> 03:39.918
Rallo, you've grown
a foot and a half.

03:39.920 --> 03:42.988
Young man, it is time
I give you another haircut.

03:42.990 --> 03:45.740
No offense, Mama, but I'm ready
to get a real haircut

03:45.742 --> 03:48.210
from someone who's qualified
to cut hair.

03:48.212 --> 03:51.263
Oh, so suddenly my masters
in cosmetology means nothing?

03:51.265 --> 03:54.767
Yeah, suddenly.

03:54.769 --> 03:57.369
Well, then I guess I can't help
you with that.

03:57.371 --> 03:59.437
Little smart-ass.

03:59.439 --> 04:03.642
I now christen
thee <i>Beer Force One.</i>

04:03.644 --> 04:06.110
[CHEERING]

04:08.447 --> 04:10.565
Guys, wait for me!

04:12.318 --> 04:14.119
It's Lester.
What's he doing?

04:14.121 --> 04:16.955
Looks like he's jogging
and carrying a big jar of money.

04:16.957 --> 04:18.556
That's how McConaughey
works out.

04:18.558 --> 04:19.825
I'm in!

04:19.827 --> 04:23.178
I knew you'd come around.
We need you.

04:23.180 --> 04:25.363
Give me your hand!

04:25.365 --> 04:27.315
[♪]

04:28.567 --> 04:30.436
Cleveland, slow down a little.

04:34.824 --> 04:36.357
He's not gonna make it!

04:36.359 --> 04:38.160
The hell he's not.

04:38.162 --> 04:41.363
I'm gonna slow down
a little more.

04:49.639 --> 04:52.474
[GRUNTING]
Oh. Oh.

04:52.476 --> 04:54.676
[BOTH SOBBING]

04:57.663 --> 05:00.848
[POP MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

05:00.850 --> 05:04.002
Two lights, two regulars.
Two lights, two regulars.

05:06.672 --> 05:07.639
We're tapped out.

05:07.641 --> 05:11.009
Sorry, folks.
That's all for today.

05:11.011 --> 05:13.044
MAN:
Come on.

05:13.046 --> 05:15.680
We've really done
something here today.

05:15.682 --> 05:19.318
TIM:
Guys, you might wanna come out
here and take a look at this.

05:22.438 --> 05:25.273
[PEOPLE GROANING]

05:25.275 --> 05:28.743
Oh, well. I guess we've learned
not to invest our own money

05:28.745 --> 05:30.545
in our harebrained ideas.

05:30.547 --> 05:31.847
Good night, everybody.

05:31.849 --> 05:33.215
Whoa, whoa, Cleveland.

05:33.217 --> 05:35.283
I put everything
I had into this truck.

05:35.285 --> 05:37.285
I'm screwed. Bankrumpt.

05:37.287 --> 05:38.753
It's "rupt."

05:39.922 --> 05:41.622
Hey,
you guys moving?

05:41.624 --> 05:43.558
What? No.
I told you Cleveland.

05:43.560 --> 05:45.727
We've lost everything
and it's all your fault.

05:45.729 --> 05:48.263
You tricked me with your
Obama-like eloquence,

05:48.265 --> 05:50.232
and "tell you no lie" mustache.

05:50.234 --> 05:52.534
Ma'am, we're gonna
need your Rascal.

05:52.536 --> 05:55.103
Oh, not the Rascal!

05:55.105 --> 05:56.138
I'm sorry.

05:56.140 --> 05:57.772
[GRUNTING]
[WHIMPERING]

05:57.774 --> 06:01.543
Hey, Tony, we got a fatty.
Little bologna here?

06:01.545 --> 06:02.544
[GROWLS]

06:02.546 --> 06:04.846
Oh.

06:04.848 --> 06:07.916
You come back here
with that bologna.

06:18.427 --> 06:20.161
There goes your house.

06:20.163 --> 06:23.632
Kendra, I'll do whatever
it takes to make this right.

06:23.634 --> 06:25.967
I'll be at mother's.

06:27.036 --> 06:29.137
[GRUNTING]

06:29.139 --> 06:32.006
Thanks a lot, Cleveland.

06:38.414 --> 06:39.781
Oh. Leak.

06:43.202 --> 06:44.286
MAN [ON TV]:
<i>And they're off.</i>

06:44.288 --> 06:45.787
Hey.

06:45.789 --> 06:47.623
Murray.
And a black kid.

06:47.625 --> 06:53.194
Boys, this is my friend, Rallo,
and he needs a man's haircut.

06:53.196 --> 06:55.163
Rallo, this is Vinnie.

06:55.165 --> 06:57.448
Oh, Rallo. Forget about it.

06:57.450 --> 06:59.417
Well, that seems authentic.

06:59.419 --> 07:00.969
Hey, grab a magazine

07:00.971 --> 07:03.538
and tell me what
we're doing today.

07:03.540 --> 07:07.742
Just take me back down
to a Lionel Jefferson.

07:11.030 --> 07:12.764
Whoa, these ladies are naked.

07:12.766 --> 07:15.200
I mean, I've seen plenty
of naked ladies in my--

07:15.202 --> 07:18.003
Oh, she ain't got no wiener.
What happened to her wiener?

07:18.005 --> 07:19.838
Someone got it.

07:19.840 --> 07:22.473
Just like I got your nose.

07:22.475 --> 07:25.010
[CHUCKLES]

07:25.012 --> 07:27.312
She never had a wiener, did she?

07:27.314 --> 07:30.648
She's had lots
of wieners, Rallo.

07:30.650 --> 07:32.567
[♪]

07:34.070 --> 07:36.071
[KENDRA GRUNTING]

07:39.575 --> 07:42.477
Oh, hey, it's you.
You ever catch that bologna?

07:42.479 --> 07:43.845
Read this.

07:45.197 --> 07:47.816
"Blah, blah, blah, failure.

07:47.818 --> 07:50.786
"Blah, blah, blah,
life not worth living.

07:50.788 --> 07:52.120
Blah, blah, blah, blah."

07:52.122 --> 07:53.789
Misspelled "suicide."

07:53.791 --> 07:55.390
Who is this even from?

07:55.392 --> 07:58.443
It's from Lester,
and he says he's driving

07:58.445 --> 08:02.247
your dang beer truck
over Suicide Falls.

08:02.249 --> 08:05.767
My deposit! And Lester.

08:05.769 --> 08:08.403
[♪]

08:16.495 --> 08:19.581
Oh, there he is!

08:21.000 --> 08:22.551
He might make it across.

08:26.688 --> 08:28.356
Nope. He gone.

08:32.845 --> 08:35.797
[PLAYING COUNTRY MUSIC]

08:38.634 --> 08:43.471
We gather here today to mourn
the loss of Lester Krinklesac.

08:43.473 --> 08:45.740
One could never know what
would drive a man

08:45.742 --> 08:47.309
to take his own life.

08:47.311 --> 08:49.944
Oh, wait. I have
his suicide note right here.

08:49.946 --> 08:51.513
Let me read it.

08:51.515 --> 08:52.914
Huh.

08:52.916 --> 08:55.567
Apparently,
he met financial ruin

08:55.569 --> 08:57.803
after some damn fool
convinced him

08:57.805 --> 09:00.605
to invest in a,
get this, beer truck.

09:00.607 --> 09:03.824
Oh, boy. Here we go.
Blame the beer truck.

09:03.826 --> 09:05.576
I do not blame the beer truck,

09:05.578 --> 09:07.946
but the greed
and the dumb-ass-itude

09:07.948 --> 09:10.548
of whoever was behind
the beer truck.

09:10.550 --> 09:14.802
Swearing during a funeral.
He's swearing during a funeral.

09:14.804 --> 09:17.572
I know.
I just feel so terrible.

09:17.574 --> 09:20.508
He was my friend,
and I made him do this.

09:20.510 --> 09:22.277
Yes, you did.

09:22.279 --> 09:26.381
You killed this man as surely
as Cain killed Abel

09:26.383 --> 09:28.783
or Ebert killed Siskel!

09:28.785 --> 09:32.853
Two thumbs down to the serpent
who led Lester astray,

09:32.855 --> 09:35.790
for he shall burn in hell!

09:35.792 --> 09:37.175
[SOBBING]

09:37.177 --> 09:40.579
Ahem. Well, at least
we'll be in hell together.

09:40.581 --> 09:41.779
Me? Why?

09:41.781 --> 09:44.316
Because of all
your texting and driving.

09:44.318 --> 09:45.983
Driving is boring.

09:47.169 --> 09:48.402
You did this.

09:48.404 --> 09:50.672
All right. Drive safe.

09:51.857 --> 09:54.576
You know, we should offer
to take her in.

09:54.578 --> 09:58.580
Or at least make
an empty gesture.

09:58.582 --> 10:00.832
Hey, Kiki,
taking a little break?

10:00.834 --> 10:03.635
Well, being a widow
ain't as glamorous

10:03.637 --> 10:05.737
as Courtney Love makes it look.

10:05.739 --> 10:07.239
Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

10:07.241 --> 10:10.475
So, Kendra, you need a place
to stay or, no, you're fine?

10:10.477 --> 10:13.862
Fine. I wouldn't wanna
be a burden.

10:13.864 --> 10:15.163
Then say no.

10:15.165 --> 10:18.683
But then again, if it will ease
some of your guilt,

10:18.685 --> 10:21.086
I suppose it's
the least I can do.

10:21.088 --> 10:23.554
DONNA [IN THE DISTANCE]:
The least you can
do is not do it.

10:23.556 --> 10:26.224
Donna, she is
a shamefully obese widow.

10:26.226 --> 10:27.892
She's staying with us.

10:27.894 --> 10:29.560
By the way, how's Ernie?

10:29.562 --> 10:32.597
He's away at the job he took
when we lost the money.

10:34.050 --> 10:35.850
[ALL GRUNTING]

10:39.505 --> 10:42.840
Oh, God! My legs!

10:42.842 --> 10:44.008
[ALL SCREAMING]

10:44.010 --> 10:45.877
Never a dull moment, huh?

10:47.179 --> 10:48.613
[MAN SCREAMING]

10:48.615 --> 10:51.265
[CHEERING]

10:51.267 --> 10:52.600
[LAUGHING]

10:52.602 --> 10:54.435
You boys watching
<i>The Squeakquel?</i>

10:54.437 --> 10:56.204
No, I was just telling
them a joke

10:56.206 --> 10:57.972
I heard at Murray's barbershop.

10:57.974 --> 11:01.392
Suffice it to say, it has to do
with a traveling salesman,

11:01.394 --> 11:03.227
and a farmer's
daughter with teeth

11:03.229 --> 11:05.664
in a place you might not expect.

11:05.666 --> 11:08.383
[LAUGHING]

11:08.385 --> 11:10.235
Agh!
You are not to set foot

11:10.237 --> 11:12.937
in that disgusting
barbershop ever again.

11:12.939 --> 11:15.023
Oh, man.
Murray and his friends

11:15.025 --> 11:16.892
are so lucky
their mamas are dead.

11:16.894 --> 11:18.626
Oh, damn, Rallo.

11:18.628 --> 11:20.095
I know.
I shouldn't have said it.

11:20.097 --> 11:22.197
God, please don't take my mama.

11:22.199 --> 11:25.133
[♪]

11:28.570 --> 11:30.655
Miss Kendra ate
all the marshmallows

11:30.657 --> 11:31.857
out of my cereal.

11:31.859 --> 11:34.759
That's just fantastic.
Sorry, Junior.

11:34.761 --> 11:36.794
But she's only here
for a few days,

11:36.796 --> 11:40.965
and, actually, some people eat
cereal without marshmallows.

11:40.967 --> 11:44.819
Well, not me. The floor can have
this because it's useless.

11:44.821 --> 11:48.055
I'm going to Denny's
for some pancakes.

11:48.057 --> 11:50.825
Did somebody say pancakes?

11:50.827 --> 11:52.527
Oh, man.

11:55.982 --> 11:59.817
KENDRA:
Oh, oh, Cleveland.

11:59.819 --> 12:01.385
Check it, homes.

12:01.387 --> 12:04.488
Your air mattress
done went flat on me.

12:04.490 --> 12:06.590
That wasn't
an air mattress.

12:06.592 --> 12:10.761
It was a $1500
Sealy Posturepedic pillow top.

12:10.763 --> 12:14.232
Well, now it's a flat toilet.
Oh, God.

12:14.234 --> 12:17.151
[♪]

12:18.387 --> 12:22.423
Oh, I gotta get back
to that barbershop.

12:23.476 --> 12:25.644
Hold still, Legolas.

12:25.646 --> 12:28.279
We don't want your silky,
flaxen tresses

12:28.281 --> 12:29.948
to get caught in your bowstring,

12:29.950 --> 12:32.817
at the Battle of Helm's Deep.

12:32.819 --> 12:36.954
Or maybe I'll bring
the barbershop to me.

12:36.956 --> 12:38.790
You're pretty.

12:38.792 --> 12:41.459
Prettier than I'll ever be.

12:41.461 --> 12:43.461
[GRUNTING]

12:46.031 --> 12:47.131
[CHUCKLES]

12:47.133 --> 12:48.299
I'm just playing.

12:48.301 --> 12:51.219
[♪]

12:51.221 --> 12:55.039
Yes, Kendra. I've come all the
way to the Fluvanna County Mall,

12:55.041 --> 12:58.543
and you're right,
they do make Kevlar pantyhose.

12:58.545 --> 13:00.912
[SIGHS]

13:05.801 --> 13:08.903
Mannish by Hilary Swank?

13:08.905 --> 13:10.187
Lester?

13:10.189 --> 13:12.724
Oh, my God, Lester.
You're alive.

13:12.726 --> 13:14.592
Pardon me, my dear sir.

13:14.594 --> 13:17.895
But I do believe you have
me confused with someone else.

13:17.897 --> 13:23.351
As you can see here on
my nameplate, my name is Lestah.

13:23.353 --> 13:25.419
I'm sorry. I had you
confused with some--

13:25.421 --> 13:26.888
Ah-ha!

13:26.890 --> 13:28.005
[SHRIEKS]

13:28.007 --> 13:31.976
I got Swank eye.
I reek of false humility.

13:31.978 --> 13:33.594
Lester, wait.

13:33.596 --> 13:35.897
I'll buy two bottles
of that cologne.

13:35.899 --> 13:37.381
You mean it?
Yes.

13:37.383 --> 13:39.567
You buy three
you get a folding umbrella.

13:39.569 --> 13:40.835
I don't need three.

13:40.837 --> 13:42.703
Lester, you've gotta come home.

13:42.705 --> 13:44.139
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

13:44.141 --> 13:46.374
All right, I'll buy three.

13:48.544 --> 13:50.245
But, Lester, how did you do it?

13:50.247 --> 13:52.947
I mean, I saw you drive
over that cliff.

13:52.949 --> 13:55.333
You saw what
looked like me appear

13:55.335 --> 13:57.802
to drive over
what seemed like a cliff.

13:57.804 --> 13:59.553
Actually, it was a cliff.

13:59.555 --> 14:02.056
That was probably confusing.
Here, let me explain.

14:02.058 --> 14:04.075
LESTER:
<i>As the truck headed</i>
<i>toward the cliff,</i>

14:04.077 --> 14:07.211
<i>I deftly maneuvered</i>
<i>the door lock mechanism</i>

14:07.213 --> 14:09.096
<i>into its unlock mode.</i>

14:09.098 --> 14:11.082
<i>Then, I wrapped my fingers</i>

14:11.084 --> 14:14.051
<i>around the door release lever</i>
<i>and applied pressure,</i>

14:14.053 --> 14:16.954
<i>causing the door to swing free</i>
<i>on its hinges.</i>

14:16.956 --> 14:18.289
<i>With no time to spare,</i>

14:18.291 --> 14:20.191
<i>I sent an electrical impulse</i>

14:20.193 --> 14:22.042
<i>from my brain</i>
<i>to my leg muscles,</i>

14:22.044 --> 14:25.312
<i>instructing them to extend</i>
<i>quickly and forcefully,</i>

14:25.314 --> 14:29.984
<i>thus propelling my body</i>
<i>out of the vehicle.</i>

14:29.986 --> 14:32.320
So you jumped out of the truck.
Yup.

14:32.322 --> 14:34.822
And you faked
your death. But why?

14:34.824 --> 14:35.956
[SIGHS]

14:35.958 --> 14:37.859
Haven't you ever
felt like the world

14:37.861 --> 14:39.293
would be better off without you?

14:40.629 --> 14:41.780
[♪]

14:41.782 --> 14:44.782
♪ My name is Glenn Quagmire
And I say ♪

14:44.784 --> 14:46.117
♪ Gig-ged-dee

14:46.119 --> 14:48.520
♪ Gig-geddy-gig-ged-dee

14:48.522 --> 14:50.755
♪ Giggy-giggy-giggy
Ged-dee ♪

14:50.757 --> 14:54.008
No. The world needs me.

14:54.010 --> 14:55.560
[♪]

14:55.562 --> 14:57.161
LESTER:
Well, here it is.

14:57.163 --> 15:00.431
Check it out, Cleveland.
Futon, not too bad.

15:00.433 --> 15:02.834
Mini-fridge, not too bad.

15:02.836 --> 15:05.937
My roommate, Dean Cain, bad.

15:05.939 --> 15:09.724
Your wife needs you, and I need
you to get her out of my house.

15:09.726 --> 15:12.493
She's turned the place
into Jabba's Palace.

15:12.495 --> 15:14.428
[DRUMS BEATING]
Yum, yum.

15:14.430 --> 15:15.596
Agh!

15:15.598 --> 15:19.500
[LAUGHING]

15:19.502 --> 15:21.269
That was the whole joke?

15:21.271 --> 15:23.104
Oh, I sat
in the damn makeup chair

15:23.106 --> 15:24.705
for seven hours for this.

15:24.707 --> 15:26.474
Look, I've been with Kendra

15:26.476 --> 15:28.276
since my sophomore year
in high school,

15:28.278 --> 15:30.044
when she was
my guidance counselor.

15:30.046 --> 15:33.447
She guided me to drop out
of school and shack up with her.

15:33.449 --> 15:35.516
She was
a horrible guidance counselor.

15:35.518 --> 15:37.051
My point is,

15:37.053 --> 15:40.638
I've never had a chance to live
on my own without Kendra.

15:40.640 --> 15:43.874
And I found out it's great.
I can do whatever I want.

15:43.876 --> 15:47.428
Don't you get it? When I died,
I finally felt alive.

15:47.430 --> 15:49.630
And I'm never going back.

15:49.632 --> 15:53.534
Well, I guess the Lester
I knew is dead.

15:53.536 --> 15:54.852
Goodbye, Cleveland.

15:54.854 --> 15:57.388
You better get out of here
before Dean Cain gets home.

15:57.390 --> 16:00.358
He is a horrible human being.

16:02.244 --> 16:04.412
Kids, good news.
[SNORING]

16:04.414 --> 16:07.515
Bomb threat at the school.
Mama's home early.

16:07.517 --> 16:08.649
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO]

16:08.651 --> 16:10.584
Sweet pearls and Jheri curls!

16:10.586 --> 16:12.336
Here's your cut, big man.

16:12.338 --> 16:16.073
Oh, boy.
Thanks, Mr. Rallo.

16:16.075 --> 16:17.558
Mama.

16:22.097 --> 16:24.799
Rallo, why are all
these men in my kitchen?

16:24.801 --> 16:25.617
[GASPS]

16:25.619 --> 16:27.418
Are they smoking my cigars?

16:27.420 --> 16:29.737
Miss Donna,
you need to relax.

16:29.739 --> 16:33.440
Have a seat, honey.
My chair is a no-stress zone.

16:33.442 --> 16:37.178
Uh-uh. Junior, nobody touches
my hair. Not even me.

16:37.180 --> 16:40.898
Shh. Shh. Shh.

16:40.900 --> 16:42.700
We all know it's a wig.

16:42.702 --> 16:46.403
Now, let's see what we can do
with what God gave you.

16:46.405 --> 16:48.890
[♪]

17:00.686 --> 17:03.555
Well, what do you think?

17:03.557 --> 17:06.290
Ooh, I look like Beyoncé.
Well...

17:09.177 --> 17:11.011
[GRUNTING]

17:11.013 --> 17:13.481
Kiki, this is very hard.

17:13.483 --> 17:16.734
I have no idea how to tell you
that Lester's alive.

17:16.736 --> 17:19.838
But, what I wanna say is--
Lester's alive?

17:19.840 --> 17:21.940
Oh, see, she already knows.

17:21.942 --> 17:24.608
And here I am walking
on eggshells.

17:24.610 --> 17:28.512
And bacon and garlic toast
and chili cheese fries.

17:28.514 --> 17:29.881
And what's that green thing?

17:29.883 --> 17:32.283
Piece of lettuce
I picked off a burger.

17:32.285 --> 17:34.285
[♪]

17:34.287 --> 17:36.654
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

17:39.758 --> 17:43.544
Mama, look at all these women.
You've ruined my barbershop.

17:43.546 --> 17:47.548
Just like that <i>Beauty Shop</i> movie
ruined the <i>Barbershop</i> franchise.

17:47.550 --> 17:49.683
Again, Rallo,
just because we're black,

17:49.685 --> 17:51.419
that doesn't mean
we have to pretend

17:51.421 --> 17:53.254
<i>Barbershop</i> was a good movie.

17:53.256 --> 17:55.573
Oh, heck with this.
I'm going back to Vinnie's.

17:55.575 --> 17:58.275
You most certainly
are not, young man.

17:58.277 --> 18:01.496
Oh, I'm not? You realize Junior
answers to me.

18:01.498 --> 18:04.898
If I say the word, you go back
to looking like James Brown.

18:04.900 --> 18:07.502
<i>♪ Hit me</i>

18:07.504 --> 18:09.036
Fine, go.

18:09.038 --> 18:12.256
Look who's back,
you old buzzards.

18:12.258 --> 18:14.208
I'm sorry.
Our memories are not what--

18:14.210 --> 18:15.543
It's Rallo.

18:15.545 --> 18:17.878
Rallo.
Hey, Rallo.

18:17.880 --> 18:19.413
[ALL COUGHING]

18:19.415 --> 18:21.282
Hey, Rallo.
Here's a 20.

18:21.284 --> 18:22.749
Run down
to the liquor store

18:22.751 --> 18:24.318
and pick us up
a bottle of gin,

18:24.320 --> 18:26.587
a bottle of Scotch
and a box of matches,

18:26.589 --> 18:27.989
so you got something
to play with

18:27.991 --> 18:30.024
while we get drunk
and take our naps.

18:30.026 --> 18:32.877
All right.

18:32.879 --> 18:35.479
Hm. I'm gonna try something.

18:37.683 --> 18:40.017
Look who's back,
you old buzzards.

18:40.019 --> 18:42.186
I'm sorry, our memories
are not what--

18:42.188 --> 18:43.487
It's Rallo.

18:43.489 --> 18:45.456
Rallo.
Hey, Rallo.

18:45.458 --> 18:46.557
[ALL COUGHING]

18:46.559 --> 18:47.658
Hey, give me 20 bucks.

18:47.660 --> 18:49.160
I'll run down
to the liquor store,

18:49.162 --> 18:51.462
and pick up a bottle of gin
and a bottle of Scotch.

18:51.464 --> 18:52.830
Good idea.

18:52.832 --> 18:54.581
[♪]

18:54.583 --> 18:57.602
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

18:57.604 --> 18:59.604
Hey, Cleveland.
I'm glad you came back.

18:59.606 --> 19:02.756
I forgot to show you something.

19:02.758 --> 19:05.626
Just got this.
They call it a shower curtain.

19:05.628 --> 19:07.228
I reckon
it's so when you pee,

19:07.230 --> 19:08.696
it don't spray
all over the floor.

19:08.698 --> 19:10.064
Lester, listen.

19:10.066 --> 19:12.150
There's someone
who wants to talk to you.

19:17.605 --> 19:19.139
[GRUNTING]

19:19.141 --> 19:21.175
[GRUNTING]

19:27.315 --> 19:28.532
Kendra.

19:28.534 --> 19:32.119
Lester Krinklesac,
you pack your stuff,

19:32.121 --> 19:34.621
and you get your skinny behind

19:34.623 --> 19:37.391
back to our home right now.
[MEN GRUNTING]

19:37.393 --> 19:39.426
I'm tired of you telling
me what to do.

19:39.428 --> 19:41.128
I'm in charge here.

19:41.130 --> 19:43.414
I have my freedom.
I have my self-respect.

19:43.416 --> 19:47.218
And I have a jar of mayonnaise
without finger marks inside it.

19:47.220 --> 19:50.488
Mayonnaise is a finger food.
MAN: Talk faster.

19:50.490 --> 19:52.423
You know why I took
that money, Kendra?

19:52.425 --> 19:54.792
Because I thought that
if this beer truck worked,

19:54.794 --> 19:57.295
I'd have finally done
something that you're proud of.

19:57.297 --> 20:00.080
And you'd start respecting me.

20:00.082 --> 20:01.282
You're right.

20:01.284 --> 20:04.051
I don't respect you
like I should,

20:04.053 --> 20:07.639
but I'm gonna
start trying really hard.

20:07.641 --> 20:09.640
[MEN GRUNTING]

20:09.642 --> 20:11.159
[MEN GRUNTING, GROANING]

20:11.161 --> 20:12.460
MAN:
Together!

20:12.462 --> 20:14.695
I'm sorry, Lester.

20:14.697 --> 20:16.531
I love you.

20:16.533 --> 20:19.166
I'll do whatever it takes
to get you to come back

20:19.168 --> 20:22.870
and stay on Cleveland's couch
with me for the next few months.

20:22.872 --> 20:24.071
[GROANS]

20:24.073 --> 20:26.557
Oh, Lester.

20:26.559 --> 20:28.842
MAN 1: Don't do that!
MAN 2: We're losing her.

20:28.844 --> 20:29.777
Mm.
[MEN YELLING]

20:29.779 --> 20:31.845
[YELLING]
[CRASHING]

20:31.847 --> 20:33.614
Kendra!
I'm okay.

20:33.616 --> 20:36.016
But both my legs is broken.

20:36.018 --> 20:38.585
And I crushed Dean Cain.

20:38.587 --> 20:41.488
No one will miss him.
And we'll sue the movers.

20:41.490 --> 20:42.522
[CHUCKLES]

20:42.524 --> 20:44.125
We're back in business.

20:44.127 --> 20:46.026
Cleveland, we're going home.

20:46.028 --> 20:49.463
Hooray, everything worked
out for everybody!

20:54.519 --> 20:58.088
Hey, look. Them fins remind me
of that movie.

20:58.090 --> 21:00.057
♪ Da-da-dum-dum
Ba-da-bum-bum ♪

21:00.059 --> 21:01.658
♪ Ba-ba-bum-bum
Ba-da-bum-bum ♪

21:01.660 --> 21:02.760
♪ Ba-ba-bum-bum

21:05.747 --> 21:07.748
[♪]

